summary:
17. Requests the Secretary-General to keep the Security Council informed and submit a report by 15 October 2010.
The Security Council:

 Requests the Secretary-General to submit a report by 26 January 2011 on possible adjustments to UNMIT's mandate and strength;

 Reaffirms the importance of the medium-term strategy and benchmarks for measuring progress in Timor-Leste and assessing UN support, and underlines the importance of ownership of the strategy by Timor-Leste's leaders and people;

 Decides to remain seized of the matter.
